modules.description: This module implements asynchronous producers and consumers for interacting with Apache Kafka, enabling message production to specific topics and partitions with optional keys, and reading messages from topics via asynchronous pipes. It supports creating and managing Kafka producers and consumers with configuration parameters, as well as defining topics with custom settings. Concrete use cases include building event-driven systems, real-time data pipelines, and distributed logging services where asynchronous messaging is required.
